io.orchestrate.client

Class KvPurgeOperation

  • java.lang.Object
    • io.orchestrate.client.KvPurgeOperation

  • public final class KvPurgeOperation
extends java.lang.Object
    Purge a KV object from a collection in the Orchestrate.io service. This will permanently remove the record from the service, and cannot be undone.

    Usage: 

     KvPurgeOperation kvPurgeOp = new KvPurgeOperation("myCollection", "someKey");
 Future<Boolean> futureResult = client.execute(deleteOp);
 Boolean result = futureResult.get();
 if (result)
     System.out.println("Successfully purged 'someKey'.");

      Create a new KvDeleteOperation to remove the object with the specified key from the collection if and only if the currentRef matches the current stored ref.
